---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Content Rights — SFCE Learning"
  description="Content rights and third-party content notices for SFCE Learning, the open-source web study guide for the Symfony Framework Certification Exam."
  canonicalPath="/content-rights/"
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 sm:py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-2">Content Rights and Third-Party Content</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary dark:text-dark-text-secondary mb-8">
      <strong class="text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary">Last updated:</strong> May 8, 2026
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-text-secondary dark:text-dark-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        SFCE Learning (<a href="https://sfcelearning.com" class="text-accent dark:text-dark-accent hover:underline">sfcelearning.com</a>)
        is a free, open-source web study guide for developers preparing for the Symfony Framework
        Certification Exam. This page explains what content is included on the website, what content
        is linked from external sources, and how third-party rights are handled.
      </p>
      <p>
        This document is provided for transparency and is not legal advice.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Summary</h2>
        <p>
          SFCE Learning is an independent study tool. The website organizes Symfony certification
          preparation into versions, topics, chapters, and curated reference links to public
          documentation.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">The website has the necessary rights to the content it includes because:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>The study guide structure, topic organization, and progress experience are original SFCE Learning content.</li>
          <li>The guide includes curated links to external Symfony documentation and related technical resources instead of republishing those external pages on this site.</li>
          <li>Symfony documentation is published under the Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported License.</li>
          <li>Symfony source code is published under the MIT License.</li>
          <li>The website uses the word "Symfony" descriptively to identify the framework, documentation, and certification topic it helps users study.</li>
          <li>SFCE Learning is not affiliated with, endorsed by, sponsored by, or officially connected to Symfony SAS or SensioLabs.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Study Guide Content</h2>
        <p>
          The website organizes Symfony certification preparation into Symfony versions, topics,
          chapters, and reference links. It is intended to help users navigate public documentation
          and track their learning progress in their own browser.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The website does not claim ownership of Symfony, PHP, public technical facts, official
          documentation, or general programming concepts.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The selection, organization, metadata, user experience, and compiled guide structure are
          part of SFCE Learning's authored product, except where a source repository or third-party
          license states otherwise. The full source code is available on
          <a href="https://github.com/kardasz/sfce" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent dark:text-dark-accent hover:underline">GitHub</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">External Documentation Links</h2>
        <p>
          The website includes curated reference links to external documentation and technical
          resources, primarily the official Symfony documentation and PHP documentation. These
          links open in your browser as standard outbound links.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The website does not copy or republish the full Symfony documentation pages as site
          content. External websites remain operated by their respective owners and are governed by
          their own licenses, terms, and privacy practices.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          For Symfony documentation, Symfony states that the documentation is licensed under
          Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported (CC BY-SA 3.0). That license permits
          sharing and adaptation under its attribution and share-alike conditions.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Source:
          <a href="https://symfony.com/doc/current/contributing/documentation/license.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent dark:text-dark-accent hover:underline break-all">https://symfony.com/doc/current/contributing/documentation/license.html</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Symfony Code and Documentation Licenses</h2>
        <p>Symfony publishes licensing information for its main materials:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Symfony documentation: Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported.</li>
          <li>Symfony source code: MIT License.</li>
          <li>Symfony website content: generally Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported unless stated otherwise.</li>
          <li>Symfony trademarks and logos: governed by Symfony's Trademark and Logo Policy.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Source:
          <a href="https://symfony.com/license" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent dark:text-dark-accent hover:underline">https://symfony.com/license</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Symfony Trademarks</h2>
        <p>
          "Symfony" is a trademark of Symfony SAS. SFCE Learning uses the name "Symfony" only to
          describe the framework, documentation, and certification subject that the website helps
          users study.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          SFCE Learning does not present itself as an official Symfony product, official Symfony
          certification provider, official Symfony training provider, or product endorsed by Symfony
          SAS or SensioLabs.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          SFCE Learning does not use Symfony logos unless separate written permission has been
          obtained from the appropriate rights holder.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Symfony's trademark policy is published here:
          <a href="https://symfony.com/trademark" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent dark:text-dark-accent hover:underline">https://symfony.com/trademark</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Quiz Content</h2>
        <p>
          The website does not currently include a knowledge quiz. The site is a curated database of
          reference links and a progress tracker only.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          A knowledge quiz is planned for the future. If a quiz is added, the questions, answer
          options, and explanations will be original study content authored for SFCE Learning, and
          this page will be updated with the relevant rights notice. The native
          <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}app/`} class="text-accent dark:text-dark-accent hover:underline">SFCE Learning app</a>
          for iPhone, iPad, and Mac already includes such a quiz; see the
          <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}app/content-rights/`} class="text-accent dark:text-dark-accent hover:underline">app's content rights page</a>
          for details.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Non-Affiliation Statement</h2>
        <p>
          SFCE Learning is an independent study tool and is not affiliated with, endorsed by,
          sponsored by, or officially connected to Symfony SAS, SensioLabs, or the official Symfony
          Certification program.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Symfony is a trademark of Symfony SAS. Other names, trademarks, and logos belong to their
          respective owners.
        </p>
      </section>

      <p class="pt-4">
        See also the <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}privacy/`} class="text-accent dark:text-dark-accent hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
